The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Sept. 23: Funds raised as external commercial borrowings (ECB) declined 64 per cent during 2008-09 on account of tight liquidity in the global markets. The net ECB flows in the country declined to $8.2 billion in 2008-09 from $22.6 billion a year ago, the finance ministry said.                             
	 New Delhi, Sept. 23: A record addition of 15 million wireless telephone users in August has catapulted the total subscriber base in the country to 494.07 million, closer to the governments 2012 target, the Telecom Regulatory Authority of India said.                             
	 New Delhi, Sept. 23: The Pension Fund Regulatory and Development Authority will announce within a month the guidelines for managing the pension funds of companies. This will extend the role of the regulator, which currently manages the fund of individual employees under the new pension system.                            
	 New Delhi, Sept. 23: Companies having a net worth of over Rs 1 crore, including banks, can now qualify as an e-return intermediary and submit electronic income tax returns on behalf of the tax assessee.                            
	 Calcutta, Sept. 23: mjunction services limited has launched the countrys first and only coal spot price index, which will serve as a barometer of the coal market in India.
                                                                                                                           
